history.content: I highly doubt 61C will fill to the point where you can't get in. In the case between 61C and Stat 135, I'd say keep 135 and take your chances with 61C since there is already a waitlist for 135.

It is certainly not guaranteed that students who indicate that 61C is the least important of 5 classes they wish to enroll in will eventually be able to enroll.  It may very well work out but you need to be ok with the idea that it won't and be comfortable taking 61C a later semester to continue with your current plan.

children.subject: I don't expect 176 to have a different drop rate than other courses.
